22const char *__get_path(const char *file, bool display_prefix)
23{
24 static char res_path[PATH_MAX];
25
26 if (*file == '/' || !display_prefix || !iopc_g.prefix_dir) {
27 return file;
28 }
29
30 if (!expect(path_extend(res_path, iopc_g.prefix_dir, "%s", file) >= 0)) {
31 return NULL;
32 }
33
34 return res_path;
35}

58/* reserved keywords in field names */
59static const char * const reserved_keywords[] = {
60 /* C keywords */
61 "auto", "bool", "break", "case", "char", "const", "continue", "default",
62 "do", "double", "else", "enum", "extern", "float", "for", "goto", "if",
63 "inline", "int", "long", "register", "restrict", "return", "short",
64 "signed", "sizeof", "static", "struct", "switch", "typedef", "union",
65 "unsigned", "void", "volatile", "while",
66 /* Java and C++ keywords */
67 "abstract", "assert", "boolean", "break", "byte", "case", "catch", "char",
68 "const", "continue", "default", "do", "double", "else", "enum", "extends",
69 "false", "final", "finally", "float", "for", "friend", "goto", "if",
70 "implements", "import", "instanceof", "int", "interface", "long",
71 "mutable", "namespace", "native", "null", "operator", "package",
72 "private", "protected", "public", "return", "short", "static", "strictfp",
73 "super", "switch", "synchronized", "template", "this", "throw", "throws",
74 "transient", "true", "try", "typename", "virtual", "void", "volatile",
75 "while",
76 /* Language keywords */
77 "in", "null", "out", "throw", "interface", "module", "package",
78};

80static const char * const avoid_keywords[] = {
81 /* sadly already in use */
82 "class", "new", "delete", "explicit",
83};

87static bool warn(qv_t(iopc_attr) *nullable attrs, const char *category)
88{
89 lstr_t s = LSTR(category);
90
91 if (!attrs)
92 return true;
93
94 tab_for_each_entry(attr, attrs) {
95 if (attr->desc->id != IOPC_ATTR_NOWARN) {
96 continue;
97 }
98
99 tab_for_each_ptr(arg, &attr->args) {
100 if (lstr_equal(arg->v.s, s)) {
101 return false;
102 }
103 }
104 }
105 return true;
106}

108static int iopc_check_name(lstr_t name, qv_t(iopc_attr) *nullable attrs,
109 sb_t *nullable err)
110{
111 if (!name.len) {
112 if (err) {
113 sb_sets(err, "empty name");
114 }
115 return -1;
116 }
117
118 if (memchr(name.s, '_', name.len) &&
119 (!attrs ||
120 iopc_attr_check(attrs, IOPC_ATTR_FORCE_FIELD_NAME, NULL) < 0))
121 {
122 if (err) {
123 sb_setf(err, "%pL contains a _", &name);
124 }
125 return -1;
126 }
127 for (int i = 0; i < countof(reserved_keywords); i++) {
128 if (lstr_equal(name, LSTR(reserved_keywords[i]))) {
129 if (err) {
130 sb_setf(err, "%pL is a reserved keyword", &name);
131 }
132 return -1;
133 }
134 }
135 if (warn(attrs, "keyword")) {
136 for (int i = 0; i < countof(avoid_keywords); i++) {
137 if (lstr_equal(name, LSTR(avoid_keywords[i]))) {
138 if (err) {
139 sb_setf(err, "%pL is a keyword in some languages", &name);
140 }
141 return -1;
142 }
143 }
144 }
145
146 return 0;
147}
148
149int iopc_check_type_name(lstr_t name, sb_t *err)
150{
151 RETHROW(iopc_check_name(name, NULL, err));
152
153 /* XXX Checked by iopc_check_name(). */
154 assert (name.len);
155
156 if (!isupper(name.s[0])) {
157 if (err) {
158 sb_setf(err, "`%pL': first character should be uppercase",
159 &name);
160 }
161 return -1;
162 }
163
164 return 0;
165}
166
167int iopc_check_field_name(lstr_t name, sb_t *err)
168{
169 RETHROW(iopc_check_name(name, NULL, err));
170
171 /* XXX Checked by iopc_check_name(). */
172 assert (name.len);
173
174 if (!islower(name.s[0])) {
175 if (err) {
176 sb_sets(err, "first field name character should be lowercase");
177 }
178 return -1;
179 }
180
181 return 0;
182}

184static int check_name(const char *name, iopc_loc_t loc,
185 qv_t(iopc_attr) *attrs)
186{
187 SB_1k(err);
188
189 if (iopc_check_name(LSTR(name), attrs, &err) < 0) {
190 throw_loc("%*pM", loc, SB_FMT_ARG(&err));
191 }
192
193 return 0;
194}

196static int
197iopc_try_file(iopc_parser_t *pp, const char *dir, iopc_path_t *path,
198 iopc_pkg_t **pkgp)
199{
200 struct stat st;
201 char file[PATH_MAX];
202 const char *pkg_name = iopc_path_dot(path);
203
204 snprintf(file, sizeof(file), "%s/%s", dir, iopc_path_slash(path));
205 path_simplify(file);
206
207 if (pp->env) {
208 const char *data;
209
210 data = qm_get_def_safe(iopc_env, pp->env, pkg_name, NULL);
211 if (data) {
212 *pkgp = RETHROW_PN(iopc_parse_file(pp->includes, pp->env, file,
213 data, false));
214 return 0;
215 }
216 }
217
218 if (stat(file, &st) == 0 && S_ISREG(st.st_mode)) {
219 *pkgp = RETHROW_PN(iopc_parse_file(pp->includes, pp->env, file,
220 NULL, false));
221 return 0;
222 }
223
224 return 0;
225}

229static const char *type_to_str(unsigned type)
230{
231 switch (type) {
232 case IOPC_ATTR_T_INT: return "integer";
233 case IOPC_ATTR_T_BOOL: return "boolean";
234 case IOPC_ATTR_T_ENUM: return "enum";
235 case IOPC_ATTR_T_DOUBLE: return "double";
236 case IOPC_ATTR_T_STRING: return "string";
237 case IOPC_ATTR_T_DATA: return "data";
238 case IOPC_ATTR_T_UNION: return "union";
239 case IOPC_ATTR_T_STRUCT: return "struct";
240 case IOPC_ATTR_T_XML: return "xml";
241 case IOPC_ATTR_T_RPC: return "rpc";
242 case IOPC_ATTR_T_IFACE: return "interface";
243 case IOPC_ATTR_T_MOD: return "module";
244 case IOPC_ATTR_T_SNMP_IFACE: return "snmpIface";
245 case IOPC_ATTR_T_SNMP_OBJ: return "snmpObj";
246 case IOPC_ATTR_T_SNMP_TBL: return "snmpTbl";
247
248 case IOPC_ATTR_T_CLASS:
249 case IOPC_ATTR_T_CLASS | IOPC_ATTR_T_STRUCT:
250 return "class";
251
252 default:
253 print_error("invalid type %d", type);
254 return NULL;
255 }
256}

258static int check_attr_type_decl(iopc_attr_t *attr, iopc_attr_type_t type)
259{
260 if (!(attr->desc->flags & IOPC_ATTR_F_DECL)) {
261 throw_loc("attribute %*pM does not apply to declarations",
262 attr->loc, LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name));
263 }
264
265 if (!(attr->desc->types & type)) {
266 throw_loc("attribute %*pM does not apply to %s",
267 attr->loc, LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name),
268 type_to_str(type));
269 }
270
271 switch (attr->desc->id) {
272 case IOPC_ATTR_PRIVATE:
273 if (!(type & IOPC_ATTR_T_CLASS)) {
274 throw_loc("attribute %*pM does not apply to %s",
275 attr->loc, LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name),
276 type_to_str(type));
277 }
278 break;
279
280 default:
281 break;
282 }
283
284 return 0;
285}

287static int check_attr_type_field(iopc_attr_t *attr, iopc_field_t *f,
288 bool tdef)
289{
290 const char *tstr = tdef ? "typedefs" : "fields";
291 iopc_attr_type_t type;
292
293 if (!(attr->desc->flags & IOPC_ATTR_F_FIELD_ALL)) {
294 throw_loc("attribute %*pM does not apply to %s", attr->loc,
295 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name), tstr);
296 }
297
298 switch (f->kind) {
299 case IOP_T_DATA: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_DATA; break;
300 case IOP_T_DOUBLE: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_DOUBLE; break;
301 case IOP_T_STRING: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_STRING; break;
302 case IOP_T_XML: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_XML; break;
303 case IOP_T_STRUCT: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_STRUCT; break;
304 case IOP_T_UNION: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_UNION; break;
305 case IOP_T_ENUM: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_ENUM; break;
306 case IOP_T_BOOL: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_BOOL; break;
307 default: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_INT; break;
308 }
309
310 if (f->kind == IOP_T_STRUCT && !f->struct_def) {
311 /* struct or union or enum -> the typer will know the real type and
312 * will check this attribute in iopc_check_field_attributes */
313 return 0;
314 }
315
316 switch (f->repeat) {
317 case IOP_R_REQUIRED:
318 if (!(attr->desc->flags & IOPC_ATTR_F_FIELD_REQUIRED)) {
319 throw_loc("attribute %*pM does not apply to required %s",
320 attr->loc, LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name), tstr);
321 }
322 break;
323
324 case IOP_R_DEFVAL:
325 if (!(attr->desc->flags & IOPC_ATTR_F_FIELD_DEFVAL)) {
326 throw_loc("attribute %*pM does not apply to %s "
327 "with default value", attr->loc,
328 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name), tstr);
329 }
330 break;
331
332 case IOP_R_OPTIONAL:
333 if (!(attr->desc->flags & IOPC_ATTR_F_FIELD_OPTIONAL)) {
334 throw_loc("attribute %*pM does not apply to optional %s",
335 attr->loc, LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name), tstr);
336 }
337 break;
338
339 case IOP_R_REPEATED:
340 if (!(attr->desc->flags & IOPC_ATTR_F_FIELD_REPEATED)) {
341 throw_loc("attribute %*pM does not apply to repeated %s",
342 attr->loc, LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name), tstr);
343 }
344 break;
345 }
346
347 if (!(attr->desc->types & type)) {
348 throw_loc("attribute %*pM does not apply to %s",
349 attr->loc,
350 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name),
351 type_to_str(type));
352 }
353
354 /* Field snmp specific checks */
355 if (attr->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_SNMP_INDEX && !f->snmp_is_in_tbl) {
356 throw_loc("field '%s' does not support @snmpIndex attribute",
357 attr->loc, f->name);
358 }
359
360 return 0;
361}

363int iopc_check_field_attributes(iopc_field_t *f, bool tdef)
364{
365 const char *tstr = tdef ? "typedefs" : "fields";
366 iopc_attr_type_t type;
367 unsigned flags = 0;
368
369 switch (f->kind) {
370 case IOP_T_DATA: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_DATA; break;
371 case IOP_T_DOUBLE: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_DOUBLE; break;
372 case IOP_T_STRING: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_STRING; break;
373 case IOP_T_XML: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_XML; break;
374 case IOP_T_BOOL: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_BOOL; break;
375 case IOP_T_STRUCT: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_STRUCT; break;
376 case IOP_T_UNION: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_UNION; break;
377 case IOP_T_ENUM: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_ENUM; break;
378 default: type = IOPC_ATTR_T_INT; break;
379 }
380
381 tab_for_each_entry(attr, &f->attrs) {
382 if (!(attr->desc->types & type)) {
383 throw_loc("attribute %*pM does not apply to %s",
384 attr->loc,
385 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name),
386 type_to_str(type));
387 }
388
389 switch (f->repeat) {
390 case IOP_R_REQUIRED:
391 if (!(attr->desc->flags & IOPC_ATTR_F_FIELD_REQUIRED)) {
392 throw_loc("attribute %*pM does not apply to required %s",
393 attr->loc, LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name), tstr);
394 }
395 break;
396
397 case IOP_R_DEFVAL:
398 if (!(attr->desc->flags & IOPC_ATTR_F_FIELD_DEFVAL)) {
399 throw_loc("attribute %*pM does not apply to %s "
400 "with default value",
401 attr->loc, LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name), tstr);
402 }
403 break;
404
405 case IOP_R_OPTIONAL:
406 if (!(attr->desc->flags & IOPC_ATTR_F_FIELD_OPTIONAL)) {
407 throw_loc("attribute %*pM does not apply to optional %s",
408 attr->loc, LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name), tstr);
409 }
410 break;
411
412 case IOP_R_REPEATED:
413 if (!(attr->desc->flags & IOPC_ATTR_F_FIELD_REPEATED)) {
414 throw_loc("attribute %*pM does not apply to repeated %s",
415 attr->loc, LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name), tstr);
416 }
417 break;
418
419 default:
420 throw_loc("unknown repeat kind for field `%s`", attr->loc, f->name);
421 }
422
423 /* Field specific checks */
424 switch (attr->desc->id) {
425 case IOPC_ATTR_ALLOW:
426 case IOPC_ATTR_DISALLOW:
427 SET_BIT(&flags, attr->desc->id);
428 if (TST_BIT(&flags, IOPC_ATTR_ALLOW)
429 && TST_BIT(&flags, IOPC_ATTR_DISALLOW))
430 {
431 throw_loc("cannot use both @allow and @disallow on the same "
432 "field", attr->loc);
433 }
434
435 tab_for_each_ptr(arg, &attr->args) {
436 bool found = false;
437
438 if (type == IOPC_ATTR_T_UNION) {
439 tab_for_each_entry(uf, &f->struct_def->fields) {
440 if (strequal(uf->name, arg->v.s.s)) {
441 found = true;
442 break;
443 }
444 }
445 } else
446 if (type == IOPC_ATTR_T_ENUM) {
447 tab_for_each_entry(ef, &f->enum_def->values) {
448 if (strequal(ef->name, arg->v.s.s)) {
449 found = true;
450 break;
451 }
452 }
453 }
454
455 if (!found) {
456 throw_loc("unknown field %*pM in %s",
457 attr->loc, LSTR_FMT_ARG(arg->v.s),
458 f->type_name);
459 }
460 }
461 break;
462
463 default:
464 break;
465 }
466 }
467
468 return 0;
469}

471static iopc_attr_desc_t *add_attr(iopc_attr_id_t id, const char *name)
472{
473 iopc_attr_desc_t d;
474 uint32_t pos;
475
476 iopc_attr_desc_init(&d);
477 d.id = id;
478 d.name = LSTR(name);
479 pos = qm_put(attr_desc, &_G.attrs, &d.name, d, 0);
480
481 if (pos & QHASH_COLLISION) {
482 print_error("attribute %s already exists", name);
483 assert (false);
484 }
485 return &_G.attrs.values[pos];
486}

642 d->types |= IOPC_ATTR_T_ALL;
643 d->flags |= IOPC_ATTR_F_DECL;
644 d->types |= IOPC_ATTR_T_SNMP_IFACE;
645 d->types |= IOPC_ATTR_T_SNMP_OBJ;
646 d->types |= IOPC_ATTR_T_SNMP_TBL;
647
648 d = add_attr(IOPC_ATTR_SNMP_PARAMS_FROM, "snmpParamsFrom");
649 d->flags |= IOPC_ATTR_F_MULTI;
650 d->flags |= IOPC_ATTR_F_DECL;
651 d->types |= IOPC_ATTR_T_SNMP_IFACE;
652 ADD_ATTR_ARG(d, "param", ITOK_IDENT);
653
654 d = add_attr(IOPC_ATTR_SNMP_PARAM, "snmpParam");
655 d->flags |= IOPC_ATTR_F_DECL;
656 d->types |= IOPC_ATTR_T_SNMP_OBJ;
657
658 d = add_attr(IOPC_ATTR_SNMP_INDEX, "snmpIndex");
659 d->flags |= IOPC_ATTR_F_FIELD_ALL;
660 d->types |= IOPC_ATTR_T_ALL;
661
662 d = add_attr(IOPC_ATTR_TS_NO_COLL, "typescriptNoCollection");
663 d->flags |= IOPC_ATTR_F_DECL;
664 d->types |= IOPC_ATTR_T_STRUCT;
665 d->types |= IOPC_ATTR_T_UNION;
666
667 d = add_attr(IOPC_ATTR_FORCE_FIELD_NAME, "forceFieldName");
668 d->flags |= IOPC_ATTR_F_FIELD_ALL;
669 d->types |= IOPC_ATTR_T_ALL_FIELDS;
670#undef ADD_ATTR_ARG
671}

673static int
674check_attr_multi(qv_t(iopc_attr) *attrs, iopc_attr_t *attr, int *pos_out)
675{
676 tab_enumerate(pos, a, attrs) {
677 if (a->desc == attr->desc) {
678 /* Generic attributes share the same desc */
679 if (a->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_GENERIC) {
680 if (lstr_equal(a->real_name, attr->real_name)) {
681 throw_loc("generic attribute '%*pM' must be unique for "
682 "each IOP object", attr->loc,
683 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->real_name));
684 }
685 *pos_out = -1;
686 return 0;
687 }
688
689 if ((attr->desc->flags & IOPC_ATTR_F_MULTI)) {
690 *pos_out = pos;
691 return 0;
692 } else {
693 throw_loc("attribute %*pM must be unique", attr->loc,
694 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name));
695 }
696 }
697 }
698
699 *pos_out = -1;
700 return 0;
701}

703int
704iopc_attr_check(const qv_t(iopc_attr) *attrs, iopc_attr_id_t attr_id,
705 const qv_t(iopc_arg) **out)
706{
707 tab_for_each_entry(e, attrs) {
708 if (e->desc->id == attr_id) {
709 if (out) {
710 *out = &e->args;
711 }
712 return 0;
713 }
714 }
715 return -1;
716}

719{

721
722 RETHROW(iopc_attr_check(attrs, IOPC_ATTR_PREFIX, &args));
723 *out = t_lstr_dup(args->tab[0].v.s);
724 return 0;
725}

730static int __tk(iopc_parser_t *pp, int i, iopc_token_t **out_tk)
731{
732 qv_t(iopc_token) *tks = &pp->tokens;
733
734 while (i >= tks->len) {
735 iopc_token_t *tk;
736
737 RETHROW(iopc_next_token(pp->ld, false, &tk));
738 if (!tk) {
739 assert (tks->len && tks->tab[tks->len - 1]->token == ITOK_EOF);
740 tk = iopc_token_retain(tks->tab[tks->len - 1]);
741 }
742 qv_append(tks, tk);
743 }
744 *out_tk = tks->tab[i];
745 return 0;
746}
747#define TK(pp, i, on_error) ({ \
748 iopc_token_t *_res; \
749 \
750 if (__tk(pp, i, &_res) < 0) { \
751 on_error; \
752 assert (false); \
753 } \
754 _res; \
755})
756#define TK_N(pp, i) TK(pp, i, return -1)
757#define TK_P(pp, i) TK(pp, i, return NULL)
758
759static void DROP(iopc_parser_t *pp, int len, int offset)
760{
761 qv_t(iopc_token) *tks = &pp->tokens;
762
763 assert (offset < tks->len && len <= tks->len);
764 for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
765 iopc_token_delete(tks->tab + offset + i);
766 }
767 qv_splice(tks, offset, len, NULL, 0);
768}
769#define DROP(_pp, _len) ((DROP)(_pp, _len, 0))
770
771static int __check(iopc_parser_t *pp, int i, iopc_tok_type_t token, bool *res)
772{
773 iopc_token_t *tk = TK_N(pp, i);
774
775 *res = tk->token == token;
776 return 0;
777}
778#define CHECK(pp, i, token, on_error) ({ \
779 bool _res; \
780 \
781 if (__check(pp, i, token, &_res) < 0) { \
782 on_error; \
783 assert (false); \
784 } \
785 _res; \
786})
787#define CHECK_N(pp, i, token) CHECK(pp, i, token, return -1)
788#define CHECK_P(pp, i, token) CHECK(pp, i, token, return NULL)
789
790static int
791__check_noeof(iopc_parser_t *pp, int i, iopc_tok_type_t token, bool *res)
792{
793 iopc_token_t *tk = TK_N(pp, i);
794
795 if (tk->token == ITOK_EOF) {
796 throw_loc("unexpected end of file", tk->loc);
797 }
798 *res = tk->token == token;
799 return 0;
800}
801#define CHECK_NOEOF(pp, i, token, on_error) ({ \
802 bool _res; \
803 \
804 if (__check_noeof(pp, i, token, &_res) < 0) { \
805 on_error; \
806 assert (false); \
807 } \
808 _res; \
809})
810#define CHECK_NOEOF_N(pp, i, token) CHECK_NOEOF(pp, i, token, return -1)
811
812static int __check_kw(iopc_parser_t *pp, int i, const char *kw, bool *res)
813{
814 iopc_token_t *tk = TK_N(pp, i);
815
816 *res = tk->token == ITOK_IDENT && strequal(tk->b.data, kw);
817 return 0;
818}
819#define CHECK_KW(pp, i, kw, on_error) ({ \
820 bool _res; \
821 \
822 if (__check_kw(pp, i, kw, &_res) < 0) { \
823 on_error; \
824 assert (false); \
825 } \
826 _res; \
827})
828#define CHECK_KW_N(pp, i, kw) CHECK_KW(pp, i, kw, return -1)
829
830static int __want(iopc_parser_t *pp, int i, iopc_tok_type_t token)
831{
832 iopc_token_t *tk = TK_N(pp, i);
833
834 if (tk->token != token) {
835 t_scope;
836
837 if (tk->token == ITOK_EOF) {
838 throw_loc("unexpected end of file", tk->loc);
839 }
840 throw_loc("%s expected, but got %s instead",
841 tk->loc, t_pretty_token(token), t_pretty_token(tk->token));
842 }
843
844 return 0;
845}
846#define WANT(pp, i, token) RETHROW(__want(pp, i, token))
847#define WANT_P(pp, i, token) RETHROW_NP(__want(pp, i, token))
848
849static int __skip(iopc_parser_t *pp, iopc_tok_type_t token, bool *res)
850{
851 if (CHECK_N(pp, 0, token)) {
852 DROP(pp, 1);
853 *res = true;
854 } else {
855 *res = false;
856 }
857 return 0;
858}
859#define SKIP(pp, token, on_error) ({ \
860 bool _res; \
861 \
862 if (__skip(pp, token, &_res) < 0) { \
863 on_error; \
864 assert (false); \
865 } \
866 _res; \
867})
868#define SKIP_N(pp, token) SKIP(pp, token, return -1)
869
870static int __skip_kw(iopc_parser_t *pp, const char *kw, bool *res)
871{
872 if (CHECK_KW_N(pp, 0, kw)) {
873 DROP(pp, 1);
874 *res = true;
875 } else {
876 *res = false;
877 }
878 return 0;
879}
880#define SKIP_KW(pp, kw, on_error) ({ \
881 bool _res; \
882 \
883 if (__skip_kw(pp, kw, &_res) < 0) { \
884 on_error; \
885 assert (false); \
886 } \
887 _res; \
888})
889#define SKIP_KW_N(pp, kw) SKIP_KW(pp, kw, return -1)
890
891static int __eat(iopc_parser_t *pp, iopc_tok_type_t token)
892{
893 WANT(pp, 0, token);
894 DROP(pp, 1);
895 return 0;
896}
897#define EAT(pp, token) RETHROW(__eat(pp, token))
898#define EAT_P(pp, token) RETHROW_NP(__eat(pp, token))
899
900static int __eat_kw(iopc_parser_t *pp, const char *kw)
901{
902 iopc_token_t *tk = TK_N(pp, 0);
903
904 if (!SKIP_KW_N(pp, kw)) {
905 WANT(pp, 0, ITOK_IDENT);
906 throw_loc("%s expected, but got %s instead",
907 tk->loc, kw, tk->b.data);
908 }
909 return 0;
910}
911#define EAT_KW(pp, token) RETHROW(__eat_kw(pp, token))
912#define EAT_KW_P(pp, token) RETHROW_NP(__eat_kw(pp, token))

914static inline char *dup_ident(iopc_token_t *tk)
915{
916 return p_dup(tk->b.data, tk->b.len + 1);
917}
918static inline const char *ident(iopc_token_t *tk)
919{
920 return tk->b.data;
921}

923static int
924parse_constant_integer(iopc_parser_t *pp, int paren, uint64_t *res,
925 bool *is_signed)
926{
927 uint64_t num = 0;
928 int pos = 0;
929 iopc_token_t *tk;
930 int nparen = 1;
931
932 for (;;) {
933 tk = TK_N(pp, pos++);
934
935 switch (tk->token) {
936 case '-': case '+': case '*': case '/': case '~':
937 case '&': case '|': case '%': case '^': case '(':
938 if (tk->token == '(') {
939 nparen++;
940 }
941 if (iop_cfolder_feed_operator(pp->cfolder,
942 (iop_cfolder_op_t)tk->token) < 0)
943 {
944 throw_loc("error when feeding the constant folder with `%c'",
945 tk->loc, tk->token);
946 }
947 break;
948
949 case ')':
950 nparen--;
951 /* If we are in a function or in an attribute, check if it is the
952 * end paren */
953 if (paren == ')' && nparen == 0) {
954 goto end;
955 }
956
957 if (iop_cfolder_feed_operator(pp->cfolder,
958 (iop_cfolder_op_t)tk->token) < 0)
959 {
960 throw_loc("error when feeding the constant folder with `%c'",
961 tk->loc, tk->token);
962 }
963 break;
964
965 case ITOK_LSHIFT:
966 if (iop_cfolder_feed_operator(pp->cfolder, CF_OP_LSHIFT) < 0) {
967 throw_loc("error when feeding the constant folder with `<<'",
968 tk->loc);
969 }
970 break;
971
972 case ITOK_RSHIFT:
973 if (iop_cfolder_feed_operator(pp->cfolder, CF_OP_RSHIFT) < 0) {
974 throw_loc("error when feeding the constant folder with `>>'",
975 tk->loc);
976 }
977 break;
978
979 case ITOK_EXP:
980 if (iop_cfolder_feed_operator(pp->cfolder, CF_OP_EXP) < 0) {
981 throw_loc("error when feeding the constant folder with `**'",
982 tk->loc);
983 }
984 break;
985
986 case ITOK_INTEGER:
987 case ITOK_BOOL:
988 if (iop_cfolder_feed_number(pp->cfolder, tk->i,
989 tk->i_is_signed) < 0)
990 {
991 if (tk->i_is_signed) {
992 throw_loc("error when feeding the constant folder with "
993 "`%jd'", tk->loc, tk->i);
994 } else {
995 throw_loc("error when feeding the constant folder with "
996 "`%ju'", tk->loc, tk->i);
997 }
998 }
999 break;
1000
1001 case ITOK_IDENT:
1002 /* check for enum value or stop */
1003 {
1004 const iopc_enum_field_t *f;
1005 int qpos = qm_find(enums, &_G.enums, ident(tk));
1006
1007 if (qpos < 0) {
1008 /* XXX compatibility code which will be removed soon */
1009 if ((qpos = qm_find(enums, &_G.enums_forbidden,
1010 ident(tk))) >= 0)
1011 {
1012 f = _G.enums_forbidden.values[qpos];
1013 goto compatibility;
1014 }
1015 throw_loc("unknown enumeration value `%s'", tk->loc,
1016 ident(tk));
1017 }
1018
1019 if (qm_find(enums, &_G.enums_forbidden, ident(tk)) >= 0) {
1020 warn_loc("enum field identifier `%s` is ambiguous",
1021 tk->loc, ident(tk));
1022 }
1023
1024 f = _G.enums.values[qpos];
1025
1026 compatibility:
1027 /* feed the enum value */
1028 if (iop_cfolder_feed_number(pp->cfolder, f->value, true) < 0)
1029 {
1030 throw_loc("error when feeding the constant folder with `%d'",
1031 tk->loc, f->value);
1032 }
1033 }
1034 break;
1035
1036 default:
1037 goto end;
1038 }
1039 }
1040
1041 end:
1042 /* Let's try to get a result */
1043 if (iop_cfolder_get_result(pp->cfolder, &num, is_signed) < 0) {
1044 throw_loc("invalid arithmetic expression", TK_N(pp, 0)->loc);
1045 }
1046 DROP(pp, pos - 1);
1047
1048 *res = num;
1049 return 0;
1050}

1222static void dox_chunk_params_args_validate(dox_chunk_t *chunk)
1223{
1224 if (chunk->params_args.len == 1 && chunk->paragraphs.len) {
1225 sb_skip(&chunk->paragraphs.tab[0], chunk->paragraph0_args_len);
1226 sb_ltrim(&chunk->paragraphs.tab[0]);
1227 chunk->paragraph0_args_len = 0;
1228 }
1229}

1231static void dox_chunk_autobrief_validate(dox_chunk_t *chunk)
1232{
1233 if (chunk->first_sentence_len
1234 && isspace(chunk->paragraphs.tab[0].data[chunk->first_sentence_len]))
1235 {
1236 pstream_t tmp = ps_initsb(&chunk->paragraphs.tab[0]);
1237 sb_t paragraph0_end;
1238
1239 ps_skip(&tmp, chunk->first_sentence_len);
1240 ps_ltrim(&tmp);
1241
1242 sb_init(&paragraph0_end);
1243 sb_add_ps(&paragraph0_end, tmp);
1244
1245 sb_clip(&chunk->paragraphs.tab[0], chunk->first_sentence_len);
1246
1247 qv_insert(&chunk->paragraphs, 1, paragraph0_end);
1248 chunk->first_sentence_len = 0;
1249 }
1250}
1251
1252static void dox_chunk_push_sb(dox_chunk_t *chunk, sb_t sb)
1253{
1254 if (chunk->paragraphs.len) {
1255 if (chunk->paragraphs.tab[0].len)
1256 sb_addc(&sb, ' ');
1257 sb_addsb(&sb, &chunk->paragraphs.tab[0]);
1258 sb_wipe(&chunk->paragraphs.tab[0]);
1259 chunk->paragraphs.tab[0] = sb;
1260 } else {
1261 qv_append(&chunk->paragraphs, sb);
1262 }
1263}
1264
1265static void dox_chunk_keyword_merge(dox_chunk_t *chunk)
1266{
1267 sb_t sb;
1268
1269 if (!chunk->keyword.len)
1270 return;
1271
1272 sb_init(&sb);
1273 sb_addc(&sb, '\\');
1274 sb_add_lstr(&sb, chunk->keyword);
1275 lstr_wipe(&chunk->keyword);
1276 dox_chunk_push_sb(chunk, sb);
1277}
1278
1279static void dox_chunk_params_merge(dox_chunk_t *chunk)
1280{
1281 sb_t sb;
1282
1283 if (!chunk->params.len) {
1284 qv_deep_clear(&chunk->params_args, lstr_wipe);
1285 return;
1286 }
1287
1288 sb_init(&sb);
1289
1290 sb_addc(&sb, '[');
1291 tab_for_each_ptr(s, &chunk->params) {
1292 sb_add_lstr(&sb, *s);
1293 if (s != tab_last(&chunk->params)) {
1294 sb_adds(&sb, ", ");
1295 }
1296 }
1297 sb_addc(&sb, ']');
1298 dox_chunk_push_sb(chunk, sb);
1299
1300 qv_deep_wipe(&chunk->params, lstr_wipe);
1301 qv_deep_wipe(&chunk->params_args, lstr_wipe);
1302 chunk->paragraph0_args_len = 0;
1303}
1304
1305static void dox_chunk_merge(dox_chunk_t *eating, dox_chunk_t *eaten)
1306{
1307 if (eaten->keyword.len > 0) {
1308 dox_chunk_keyword_merge(eaten);
1309 dox_chunk_params_merge(eaten);
1310 } else {
1311 tab_for_each_entry(param, &eaten->params) {
1312 qv_append(&eating->params, param);
1313 }
1314 tab_for_each_entry(arg, &eaten->params_args) {
1315 qv_append(&eating->params_args, arg);
1316 }
1317 if (eating->paragraphs.len <= 1) {
1318 eating->paragraph0_args_len += eaten->paragraph0_args_len;
1319 }
1320 }
1321
1322 if (eating->paragraphs.len && eaten->paragraphs.len) {
1323 sb_addc(tab_last(&eating->paragraphs), ' ');
1324 sb_addsb(tab_last(&eating->paragraphs), &eaten->paragraphs.tab[0]);
1325 sb_wipe(&eaten->paragraphs.tab[0]);
1326 qv_skip(&eaten->paragraphs, 1);
1327 }
1328 tab_for_each_entry(paragraph, &eaten->paragraphs) {
1329 qv_append(&eating->paragraphs, paragraph);
1330 }
1331
1332 iopc_loc_merge(&eating->loc, eaten->loc);
1333
1334 lstr_wipe(&eaten->keyword);
1335 qv_wipe(&eaten->params);
1336 qv_wipe(&eaten->params_args);
1337 qv_wipe(&eaten->paragraphs);
1338}
1339
1340static int
1341read_dox(iopc_parser_t *pp, int tk_offset, qv_t(dox_chunk) *chunks, bool back,
1342 int ignore_token, bool *res)
1343{
1344 const iopc_token_t *tk;
1345 dox_tok_t *dox;
1346
1347 if (ignore_token && CHECK_N(pp, tk_offset, ignore_token)) {
1348 tk_offset++;
1349 }
1350
1351 tk = TK_N(pp, tk_offset);
1352 dox = tk->dox;
1353
1354 if (!CHECK_N(pp, tk_offset, ITOK_DOX_COMMENT)
1355 || (back && !dox->is_back))
1356 {
1357 *res = false;
1358 return 0;
1359 }
1360
1361 /* XXX: when reading front, back comments are forced to be front
1362 * with first chunk = "<" */
1363 if (!back && dox->is_back) {
1364 dox_chunk_t chunk;
1365
1366 dox->is_back = false;
1367 dox_chunk_init(&chunk);
1368 sb_addc(sb_init(qv_growlen(&chunk.paragraphs, 1)), '<');
1369 chunk.loc = tk->loc;
1370 chunk.loc.lmax = chunk.loc.lmin;
1371 qv_insert(&dox->chunks, 0, chunk);
1372 }
1373
1374 tab_for_each_ptr(chunk, &dox->chunks) {
1375 bool force_merge = false;
1376 dox_chunk_t *last;
1377
1378 if (chunks->len == 0) {
1379 goto append;
1380 }
1381 last = tab_last(chunks);
1382
1383 /* force merge if the chunk has a unknown keyword, so that syntax
1384 * like: "See \ref field" or "\param[in] a The \p ref" works.
1385 */
1386 if (chunk->keyword.len > 0
1387 && iopc_dox_check_keyword(chunk->keyword, NULL) < 0)
1388 {
1389 force_merge = true;
1390 }
1391
1392 /* this test is intended for first chunk of the current token */
1393 if (force_merge
1394 || (!chunk->keyword.len && chunk->loc.lmin - last->loc.lmax < 2))
1395 {
1396 dox_chunk_merge(last, chunk);
1397 continue;
1398 }
1399
1400 append:
1401 qv_append(chunks, *chunk);
1402 }
1403 (DROP)(pp, 1, tk_offset);
1404 *res = true;
1405 return 0;
1406}
1407
1408static int read_dox_front(iopc_parser_t *pp, qv_t(dox_chunk) *chunks)
1409{
1410 int offset = 0;
1411 bool read_dox_res;
1412
1413 do {
1414 /* XXX: we ignore tags when reading doxygen front comments */
1415 if (CHECK_N(pp, offset, ITOK_INTEGER)
1416 && CHECK_N(pp, offset + 1, ':'))
1417 {
1418 offset += 2;
1419 }
1420 RETHROW(read_dox(pp, offset, chunks, false, 0, &read_dox_res));
1421 } while (read_dox_res);
1422
1423 return 0;
1424}
1425
1426static int
1427read_dox_back(iopc_parser_t *pp, qv_t(dox_chunk) *chunks, int ignore_token)
1428{
1429 bool read_dox_res;
1430
1431 do {
1432 RETHROW(read_dox(pp, 0, chunks, true, ignore_token, &read_dox_res));
1433 } while (read_dox_res);
1434
1435 return 0;
1436}

1438static
1439void iopc_dox_desc_append_paragraphs(lstr_t *desc, const qv_t(sb) *paragraphs)
1440{
1441 SB_1k(text);
1442
1443 sb_add_lstr(&text, *desc);
1444 tab_for_each_ptr(paragraph, paragraphs) {
1445 if (text.len && paragraph->len) {
1446 sb_addc(&text, '\n');
1447 }
1448 sb_addsb(&text, paragraph);
1449 }
1450 lstr_wipe(desc);
1451 lstr_transfer_sb(desc, &text, false);
1452}

1454static void
1455iopc_dox_append_paragraphs_to_details(qv_t(iopc_dox) *comments,
1456 const qv_t(sb) *paragraphs)
1457{
1458 iopc_dox_t *dox;
1459
1460 if (!paragraphs->len)
1461 return;
1462
1463 dox = iopc_dox_find_type_or_create(comments, IOPC_DOX_TYPE_DETAILS);
1464 iopc_dox_desc_append_paragraphs(&dox->desc, paragraphs);
1465}
1466
1467static void
1468iopc_dox_split_paragraphs(const qv_t(sb) *paragraphs,
1469 qv_t(sb) *first, qv_t(sb) *others)
1470{
1471 if (first)
1472 qv_init_static(first, paragraphs->tab, 1);
1473
1474 if (others)
1475 qv_init_static(others, paragraphs->tab + 1, paragraphs->len - 1);
1476}
1477
1478static void
1479iopc_dox_append_paragraphs(qv_t(iopc_dox) *comments, lstr_t *desc,
1480 const qv_t(sb) *paragraphs)
1481{
1482 qv_t(sb) first;
1483 qv_t(sb) others;
1484
1485 if (!paragraphs->len)
1486 return;
1487
1488 iopc_dox_split_paragraphs(paragraphs, &first, &others);
1489
1490 iopc_dox_desc_append_paragraphs(desc, &first);
1491 iopc_dox_append_paragraphs_to_details(comments, &others);
1492}
1493
1494/* XXX: the first paragraph of a chunk could be empty
1495 * and it is the sole paragraph of a chunk that can be empty
1496 * in case it is empty we must append the paragraphs to 'details'
1497 * but only if there are others paragraphs in order to avoid an empty
1498 * 'details'
1499 */
1500static int
1501iopc_dox_check_paragraphs(qv_t(iopc_dox) *comments,
1502 const qv_t(sb) *paragraphs)
1503{
1504 if (!paragraphs->len)
1505 return -1;
1506
1507 if (paragraphs->tab[0].len)
1508 return 0;
1509
1510 if (paragraphs->len > 1) {
1511 iopc_dox_append_paragraphs_to_details(comments, paragraphs);
1512 }
1513 return -1;
1514}
1515
1516static int
1517build_dox_param(const iopc_fun_t *owner, qv_t(iopc_dox) *res,
1518 dox_chunk_t *chunk)
1519{
1520 iopc_fun_struct_type_t dir;
1521 const iopc_fun_struct_t *fun_st;
1522
1523 if (!chunk->params.len) {
1524 throw_loc("doxygen param direction not specified", chunk->loc);
1525 }
1526
1527 if (chunk->params.len > 1) {
1528 throw_loc("more than one doxygen param direction", chunk->loc);
1529 }
1530
1531 if (iopc_dox_check_param_dir(chunk->params.tab[0], &dir) < 0)
1532 {
1533 throw_loc("unsupported doxygen param direction: `%*pM`", chunk->loc,
1534 LSTR_FMT_ARG(chunk->params.tab[0]));
1535 }
1536
1537 fun_st = iopc_fun_get_struct_const(owner, dir);
1538 if (fun_st && !fun_st->is_anonymous) {
1539 qv_deep_wipe(&chunk->params_args, lstr_wipe);
1540 qv_append(&chunk->params_args, LSTR_EMPTY_V);
1541 chunk->paragraph0_args_len = 0;
1542 }
1543
1544 dox_chunk_params_args_validate(chunk);
1545
1546 if (iopc_dox_check_paragraphs(res, &chunk->paragraphs) < 0) {
1547 return 0;
1548 }
1549
1550 tab_enumerate(i, arg, &chunk->params_args) {
1551 iopc_field_t *arg_field;
1552 qv_t(sb) arg_paragraphs;
1553 qv_t(sb) object_paragraphs;
1554
1555 for (int j = i + 1; j < chunk->params_args.len; j++) {
1556 if (lstr_equal(arg, chunk->params_args.tab[j])) {
1557 throw_loc("doxygen duplicated `%*pM` argument `%*pM`",
1558 chunk->loc, LSTR_FMT_ARG(chunk->params.tab[0]),
1559 LSTR_FMT_ARG(arg));
1560 }
1561 }
1562
1563 arg_field = iopc_dox_arg_find_in_fun(arg, dir, owner);
1564 if (!arg_field) {
1565 throw_loc("doxygen unrelated `%*pM` argument `%*pM` for RPC `%s`",
1566 chunk->loc, LSTR_FMT_ARG(chunk->params.tab[0]),
1567 LSTR_FMT_ARG(arg), owner->name);
1568 }
1569
1570 iopc_dox_split_paragraphs(&chunk->paragraphs,
1571 &arg_paragraphs, &object_paragraphs);
1572
1573 iopc_dox_append_paragraphs_to_details(&arg_field->comments,
1574 &arg_paragraphs);
1575 debug_dump_dox(arg_field->comments, arg_field->name);
1576
1577 iopc_dox_append_paragraphs_to_details(res, &object_paragraphs);
1578 }
1579
1580 return 0;
1581}
1582
1583static int build_dox_(qv_t(dox_chunk) *chunks, const void *owner,
1584 int attr_type, qv_t(iopc_dox) *comments)
1585{
1586 SB(sb, 256);
1587
1588 qv_init(comments);
1589
1590 tab_for_each_ptr(chunk, chunks) {
1591 iopc_dox_t *dox = NULL;
1592 int type = -1;
1593
1594 if (chunk->keyword.len
1595 && iopc_dox_check_keyword(chunk->keyword, &type) >= 0
1596 && !iopc_dox_type_is_related(type, attr_type))
1597 {
1598 error_loc("unrelated doxygen keyword: `%*pM`", chunk->loc,
1599 LSTR_FMT_ARG(chunk->keyword));
1600 goto error;
1601 }
1602
1603 if (type == -1) {
1604 dox_chunk_params_merge(chunk);
1605 dox_chunk_keyword_merge(chunk);
1606 }
1607
1608 if (iopc_dox_check_paragraphs(comments, &chunk->paragraphs) < 0) {
1609 continue;
1610 }
1611
1612 if (type == IOPC_DOX_TYPE_PARAM) {
1613 if (build_dox_param(owner, comments, chunk) < 0) {
1614 goto error;
1615 }
1616 continue;
1617 }
1618
1619 if (type >= 0) {
1620 dox = iopc_dox_find_type_or_create(comments, type);
1621 iopc_dox_append_paragraphs(comments, &dox->desc,
1622 &chunk->paragraphs);
1623 } else
1624 if (iopc_dox_find_type(comments, IOPC_DOX_TYPE_BRIEF)) {
1625 iopc_dox_append_paragraphs_to_details(comments,
1626 &chunk->paragraphs);
1627 } else {
1628 dox = iopc_dox_add(comments, IOPC_DOX_TYPE_BRIEF);
1629 dox_chunk_autobrief_validate(chunk);
1630 iopc_dox_append_paragraphs(comments, &dox->desc,
1631 &chunk->paragraphs);
1632 }
1633
1634 if (type == IOPC_DOX_TYPE_EXAMPLE) {
1635 t_scope;
1636 const qv_t(log_buffer) *logs;
1637 int res;
1638 iopc_loc_t loc = chunk->loc;
1639 lstr_t name = t_lstr_fmt("%s[%d-%d]",
1640 loc.file, loc.lmin, loc.lmax);
1641 iopc_parser_t pp = {
1642 .cfolder = iop_cfolder_new(),
1643 .ld = iopc_lexer_new(name.s, dox->desc.s, IOPC_FILE_BUFFER)
1644 };
1645
1646 log_start_buffering(false);
1647
1648 sb_reset(&sb);
1649 sb_addc(&sb, '{');
1650 res = parse_json_object(&pp, &sb, true);
1651 sb_addc(&sb, '}');
1652
1653 logs = log_stop_buffering();
1654
1655 qv_deep_wipe(&pp.tokens, iopc_token_delete);
1656 iopc_lexer_delete(&pp.ld);
1657 iop_cfolder_delete(&pp.cfolder);
1658 if (res < 0) {
1659 if (logs->len > 0) {
1660 print_error("error: %*pM",
1661 LSTR_FMT_ARG(logs->tab[0].msg));
1662 } else {
1663 print_error("json parsing error");
1664 }
1665 goto error;
1666 }
1667 lstr_transfer_sb(&dox->desc, &sb, false);
1668 }
1669
1670 }
1671
1672 qv_deep_clear(chunks, dox_chunk_wipe);
1673 return 0;
1674
1675 error:
1676 qv_deep_clear(chunks, dox_chunk_wipe);
1677 return -1;
1678}
1679
1680#define build_dox(_chunks, _owner, _attr_type) \
1681 ({ \
1682 int _res = build_dox_(_chunks, _owner, _attr_type, \
1683 &(_owner)->comments); \
1684 \
1685 debug_dump_dox((_owner)->comments, (_owner)->name); \
1686 _res; \
1687 })
1688
1689#define build_dox_check_all(_chunks, _owner) \
1690 ({ build_dox(_chunks, _owner, -1); })

1692static iopc_attr_t *parse_attr(iopc_parser_t *pp);
1693
1694static int iopc_add_attr(qv_t(iopc_attr) *attrs, iopc_attr_t **attrp)
1695{
1696 iopc_attr_t *attr = *attrp;
1697 int pos = 0;
1698
1699 RETHROW(check_attr_multi(attrs, attr, &pos));
1700
1701 if (pos < 0 || attr->desc->args.len != 1) {
1702 qv_append(attrs, attr);
1703 } else {
1704 tab_for_each_entry(arg, &attr->args) {
1705 *qv_growlen(&attrs->tab[pos]->args, 1) =
1706 iopc_arg_dup(&arg);
1707 }
1708 iopc_attr_delete(attrp);
1709 }
1710
1711 return 0;
1712}

1714int iopc_field_add_attr(iopc_field_t *f, iopc_attr_t **attrp, bool tdef)
1715{
1716 RETHROW(check_attr_type_field(*attrp, f, tdef));
1717 RETHROW(iopc_add_attr(&f->attrs, attrp));
1718 return 0;
1719}

1721static int
1722check_dox_and_attrs(iopc_parser_t *pp, qv_t(dox_chunk) *chunks,
1723 qv_t(iopc_attr) *attrs, int attr_type)
1724{
1725 qv_clear(attrs);
1726 qv_deep_clear(chunks, dox_chunk_wipe);
1727
1728 for (;;) {
1729 if (CHECK_N(pp, 0, ITOK_ATTR)) {
1730 iopc_attr_t *attr = RETHROW_PN(parse_attr(pp));
1731
1732 if (attr_type >= 0) {
1733 if (check_attr_type_decl(attr, attr_type) < 0) {
1734 iopc_attr_delete(&attr);
1735 return -1;
1736 }
1737 }
1738 if (iopc_add_attr(attrs, &attr) < 0) {
1739 iopc_attr_delete(&attr);
1740 return -1;
1741 }
1742 } else {
1743 bool read_dox_res;
1744
1745 RETHROW(read_dox(pp, 0, chunks, false, 0, &read_dox_res));
1746 if (!read_dox_res) {
1747 break;
1748 }
1749 }
1750 }
1751
1752 return read_dox_front(pp, chunks);
1753}
1754#define check_dox_and_attrs(_pp, _chunks, _attrs) \
1755 ((check_dox_and_attrs)((_pp), (_chunks), (_attrs), -1))
1756
1757/*-}}}-*/
1758/*----- recursive descent parser -{{{-*/
1759
1760static char *iopc_upper_ident(iopc_parser_t *pp)
1761{
1762 iopc_token_t *tk = TK_P(pp, 0);
1763 char *res;
1764
1765 WANT_P(pp, 0, ITOK_IDENT);
1766 if (!isupper((unsigned char)ident(tk)[0])) {
1767 throw_loc_p("first character must be uppercase (got `%s')",
1768 tk->loc, ident(tk));
1769 }
1770 res = dup_ident(tk);
1771 DROP(pp, 1);
1772 return res;
1773}
1774
1775static char *iopc_aupper_ident(iopc_parser_t *pp)
1776{
1777 iopc_token_t *tk = TK_P(pp, 0);
1778 char *res;
1779
1780 WANT_P(pp, 0, ITOK_IDENT);
1781 for (const char *s = ident(tk); *s; s++) {
1782 if (isdigit((unsigned char)*s) || *s == '_') {
1783 continue;
1784 }
1785 if (isupper((unsigned char)*s)) {
1786 continue;
1787 }
1788 throw_loc_p("this token should be all uppercase", tk->loc);
1789 }
1790 res = dup_ident(tk);
1791 DROP(pp, 1);
1792 return res;
1793}
1794
1795static char *iopc_lower_ident(iopc_parser_t *pp)
1796{
1797 iopc_token_t *tk = TK_P(pp, 0);
1798 char *res;
1799
1800 WANT_P(pp, 0, ITOK_IDENT);
1801 if (!islower((unsigned char)ident(tk)[0])) {
1802 throw_loc_p("first character must be lowercase (got `%s')",
1803 tk->loc, ident(tk));
1804 }
1805 res = dup_ident(tk);
1806 DROP(pp, 1);
1807 return res;
1808}

1810static iopc_pkg_t *
1811check_path_exists(iopc_parser_t *pp, iopc_path_t *path)
1812{
1813 iopc_pkg_t *pkg = NULL;
1814
1815 pkg = qm_get_def(iopc_pkg, &_G.pkgs, iopc_path_dot(path), NULL);
1816 if (pkg) {
1817 return pkg;
1818 }
1819
1820 if (pp->base) {
1821 RETHROW_NP(iopc_try_file(pp, pp->base, path, &pkg));
1822 if (pkg) {
1823 return pkg;
1824 }
1825 }
1826 if (pp->includes) {
1827 tab_for_each_entry(include, pp->includes) {
1828 RETHROW_NP(iopc_try_file(pp, include, path, &pkg));
1829 if (pkg) {
1830 return pkg;
1831 }
1832 }
1833 }
1834 throw_loc_p("unable to find file `%s` in the include path",
1835 path->loc, iopc_path_slash(path));
1836}
1837
1838static iopc_path_t *parse_path_aux(iopc_parser_t *pp, iopc_pkg_t **modp)
1839{
1840 iopc_path_t *path;
1841 iopc_token_t *tk0 = TK_P(pp, 0);
1842 char *lowered;
1843
1844 path = iopc_path_new();
1845 path->loc = tk0->loc;
1846 if (!(lowered = iopc_lower_ident(pp))) {
1847 goto error;
1848 }
1849 qv_append(&path->bits, lowered);
1850
1851 while (CHECK(pp, 0, '.', goto error)
1852 && CHECK(pp, 1, ITOK_IDENT, goto error))
1853 {
1854 iopc_token_t *tk1 = TK(pp, 1, goto error);
1855
1856 if (!islower((unsigned char)ident(tk1)[0])) {
1857 break;
1858 }
1859 qv_append(&path->bits, dup_ident(tk1));
1860 iopc_loc_merge(&path->loc, tk1->loc);
1861 DROP(pp, 2);
1862 }
1863
1864 if (modp && !(*modp = check_path_exists(pp, path))) {
1865 goto error;
1866 }
1867 return path;
1868
1869 error:
1870 iopc_path_delete(&path);
1871 return NULL;
1872}
1873
1874static iopc_path_t *parse_pkg_stmt(iopc_parser_t *pp)
1875{
1876 iopc_path_t *path;
1877
1878 EAT_KW_P(pp, "package");
1879 path = RETHROW_P(parse_path_aux(pp, NULL));
1880
1881 if (CHECK(pp, 0, '.', goto error)) {
1882 if (__want(pp, 1, ITOK_IDENT) < 0) {
1883 goto error;
1884 }
1885 }
1886
1887 if (__eat(pp, ';') < 0) {
1888 goto error;
1889 }
1890
1891 return path;
1892
1893 error:
1894 iopc_path_delete(&path);
1895 return NULL;
1896}
1897
1898iop_type_t iop_get_type(lstr_t name)
1899{
1900 int v = iopc_get_token_lstr(name);
1901
1902 if (v == IOPC_TK_unknown) {
1903 return IOP_T_STRUCT;
1904 }
1905 for (const char *p = name.s; p < name.s + name.len; p++) {
1906 if (isupper(*p)) {
1907 return IOP_T_STRUCT;
1908 }
1909 }
1910 switch (v) {
1911 case IOPC_TK_BYTE: return IOP_T_I8;
1912 case IOPC_TK_UBYTE: return IOP_T_U8;
1913 case IOPC_TK_SHORT: return IOP_T_I16;
1914 case IOPC_TK_USHORT: return IOP_T_U16;
1915 case IOPC_TK_INT: return IOP_T_I32;
1916 case IOPC_TK_UINT: return IOP_T_U32;
1917 case IOPC_TK_LONG: return IOP_T_I64;
1918 case IOPC_TK_ULONG: return IOP_T_U64;
1919 case IOPC_TK_BOOL: return IOP_T_BOOL;
1920
1921 case IOPC_TK_BYTES: return IOP_T_DATA;
1922 case IOPC_TK_DOUBLE: return IOP_T_DOUBLE;
1923 case IOPC_TK_STRING: return IOP_T_STRING;
1924 case IOPC_TK_XML: return IOP_T_XML;
1925 case IOPC_TK_VOID: return IOP_T_VOID;
1926 default:
1927 return IOP_T_STRUCT;
1928 }
1929}
1930
1931static iop_type_t get_type_kind(iopc_token_t *tk)
1932{
1933 return iop_get_type(LSTR_SB_V(&tk->b));
1934}
1935
1936static int parse_struct_type(iopc_parser_t *pp, iopc_pkg_t **type_pkg,
1937 iopc_path_t **path, char **name)
1938{
1939 iopc_token_t *tk = TK_N(pp, 0);
1940
1941 WANT(pp, 0, ITOK_IDENT);
1942 if (islower((unsigned char)ident(tk)[0])) {
1943 *path = RETHROW_PN(parse_path_aux(pp, type_pkg));
1944 EAT(pp, '.');
1945 WANT(pp, 0, ITOK_IDENT);
1946 TK_N(pp, 0);
1947 }
1948 *name = RETHROW_PN(iopc_upper_ident(pp));
1949 return 0;
1950}
1951
1952int iopc_check_field_type(const iopc_field_t *f, sb_t *err)
1953{
1954 if (f->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
1955 if (f->is_static) {
1956 sb_sets(err, "optional static members are forbidden");
1957 return -1;
1958 }
1959 } else
1960 if (f->is_ref) {
1961 if (f->is_static) {
1962 sb_sets(err, "referenced static members are forbidden");
1963 return -1;
1964 }
1965 if (f->kind != IOP_T_STRUCT) {
1966 sb_sets(err,
1967 "references can only be applied to structures or unions");
1968 return -1;
1969 }
1970 if (f->repeat != IOP_R_REQUIRED) {
1971 sb_sets(err, "references can only be applied to required fields");
1972 return -1;
1973 }
1974 } else
1975 if (f->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
1976 if (f->is_static) {
1977 sb_sets(err, "repeated static members are forbidden");
1978 return -1;
1979 }
1980 if (f->kind == IOP_T_VOID) {
1981 sb_sets(err, "repeated void types are forbidden");
1982 return -1;
1983 }
1984 }
1985
1986 return 0;
1987}
1988
1989static int parse_field_type(iopc_parser_t *pp, iopc_struct_t *st,
1990 iopc_field_t *f)
1991{
1992 SB_1k(err);
1993
1994 WANT(pp, 0, ITOK_IDENT);
1995 f->kind = get_type_kind(TK_N(pp, 0));
1996
1997 /* in case of snmpObj structure, some field type are not handled */
1998 if (f->kind == IOP_T_STRUCT) {
1999 RETHROW(parse_struct_type(pp, &f->type_pkg, &f->type_path,
2000 &f->type_name));
2001 } else {
2002 DROP(pp, 1);
2003 }
2004
2005 switch (TK_N(pp, 0)->token) {
2006 case '?':
2007 f->repeat = IOP_R_OPTIONAL;
2008 DROP(pp, 1);
2009 break;
2010
2011 case '&':
2012 f->repeat = IOP_R_REQUIRED;
2013 f->is_ref = true;
2014 DROP(pp, 1);
2015 break;
2016
2017 case '[':
2018 WANT(pp, 1, ']');
2019 f->repeat = IOP_R_REPEATED;
2020 DROP(pp, 2);
2021 break;
2022
2023 default:
2024 f->repeat = IOP_R_REQUIRED;
2025 break;
2026 }
2027
2028 if (iopc_check_field_type(f, &err) < 0) {
2029 throw_loc("%*pM", f->loc, SB_FMT_ARG(&err));
2030 }
2031
2032 return 0;
2033}
2034
2035static int parse_field_defval(iopc_parser_t *pp, iopc_field_t *f, int paren)
2036{
2037 iopc_token_t *tk;
2038
2039 EAT(pp, '=');
2040 tk = TK_N(pp, 0);
2041
2042 if (f->repeat != IOP_R_REQUIRED) {
2043 throw_loc("default values for non required fields makes no sense",
2044 tk->loc);
2045 }
2046 f->repeat = IOP_R_DEFVAL;
2047
2048 if (tk->b_is_char) {
2049 WANT(pp, 0, ITOK_STRING);
2050 f->defval.u64 = (uint64_t)tk->b.data[0];
2051 f->defval_type = IOPC_DEFVAL_INTEGER;
2052 DROP(pp, 1);
2053 } else
2054 if (CHECK_N(pp, 0, ITOK_STRING)) {
2055 f->defval.ptr = p_strdup(tk->b.data);
2056 f->defval_type = IOPC_DEFVAL_STRING;
2057 DROP(pp, 1);
2058 } else
2059 if (CHECK_N(pp, 0, ITOK_DOUBLE)) {
2060 f->defval.d = tk->d;
2061 f->defval_type = IOPC_DEFVAL_DOUBLE;
2062 DROP(pp, 1);
2063 } else {
2064 bool is_signed;
2065
2066 RETHROW(parse_constant_integer(pp, paren, &f->defval.u64,
2067 &is_signed));
2068 f->defval_is_signed = is_signed;
2069 f->defval_type = IOPC_DEFVAL_INTEGER;
2070 }
2071 return 0;
2072}
2073
2074int iopc_check_tag_value(int tag, sb_t *err)
2075{
2076 if (tag < 1) {
2077 sb_setf(err, "tag is too small (must be >= 1, got %d)", tag);
2078 return -1;
2079 }
2080 if (tag >= 0x8000) {
2081 sb_setf(err, "tag is too large (must be < 0x8000, got 0x%x)", tag);
2082 return -1;
2083 }
2084
2085 return 0;
2086}
2087
2088static iopc_field_t *
2089parse_field_stmt(iopc_parser_t *pp, iopc_struct_t *st, qv_t(iopc_attr) *attrs,
2090 qm_t(iopc_field) *fields, qv_t(i32) *tags, int *next_tag,
2091 int paren, bool is_snmp_iface, bool is_rpc_arg)
2092{
2093 iopc_loc_t name_loc;
2094 iopc_field_t *f = NULL;
2095 iopc_token_t *tk;
2096 int tag;
2097
2098 f = iopc_field_new();
2099 f->loc = TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc;
2100 f->snmp_is_in_tbl = iopc_is_snmp_tbl(st->type);
2101
2102 if (SKIP_KW(pp, "static", goto error)) {
2103 if (!iopc_is_class(st->type)) {
2104 error_loc("static keyword is only authorized for class fields",
2105 f->loc);
2106 goto error;
2107 }
2108 f->is_static = true;
2109 } else {
2110 SB_1k(err);
2111
2112 /* Tag */
2113 if (CHECK(pp, 0, ITOK_INTEGER, goto error)) {
2114 if (__want(pp, 1, ':') < 0) {
2115 goto error;
2116 }
2117 tk = TK(pp, 0, goto error);
2118 f->tag = tk->i;
2119 *next_tag = f->tag + 1;
2120 DROP(pp, 2);
2121 if (CHECK_KW(pp, 0, "static", goto error)) {
2122 error_loc("tag is not authorized for static class fields",
2123 TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc);
2124 goto error;
2125 }
2126 } else {
2127 f->tag = (*next_tag)++;
2128 }
2129
2130 if (iopc_check_tag_value(f->tag, &err) < 0) {
2131 error_loc("%*pM", TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc, SB_FMT_ARG(&err));
2132 goto error;
2133 }
2134 }
2135
2136 /* If the field is contained by a snmpIface rpc struct, it will have no
2137 * type (so no need to parse the type), and the flag snmp_is_from_param
2138 * needs to be set at true */
2139 if (is_snmp_iface) {
2140 f->snmp_is_from_param = true;
2141 } else {
2142 if (parse_field_type(pp, st, f) < 0) {
2143 goto error;
2144 }
2145 if (is_rpc_arg && f->kind == IOP_T_VOID
2146 && f->repeat == IOP_R_REQUIRED)
2147 {
2148 error_loc("required void types are forbidden for rpc arguments",
2149 TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc);
2150 goto error;
2151 }
2152 }
2153
2154 if (__want(pp, 0, ITOK_IDENT) < 0) {
2155 goto error;
2156 }
2157 f->name = dup_ident(TK(pp, 0, goto error));
2158
2159 if (iopc_attr_check(attrs, IOPC_ATTR_FORCE_FIELD_NAME, NULL) < 0) {
2160 if (strchr(f->name, '_')) {
2161 error_loc("identifier '%s' contains a _",
2162 TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc, f->name);
2163 goto error;
2164 }
2165 if (!islower(f->name[0])) {
2166 error_loc("first character must be lowercased (got %s)",
2167 TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc, f->name);
2168 goto error;
2169 }
2170 }
2171
2172 name_loc = TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc;
2173 DROP(pp, 1);
2174
2175 if (CHECK(pp, 0, '=', goto error)) {
2176 if (st->type == STRUCT_TYPE_UNION) {
2177 error_loc("default values are forbidden in union types", f->loc);
2178 goto error;
2179 }
2180 if (f->kind == IOP_T_VOID) {
2181 error_loc("default values are forbidden for void types", f->loc);
2182 goto error;
2183 }
2184 if (parse_field_defval(pp, f, paren) < 0) {
2185 goto error;
2186 }
2187 assert (f->defval_type);
2188 } else
2189 if (f->is_static && !st->is_abstract) {
2190 error_loc("static fields of non-abstract classes must have a "
2191 "default value", f->loc);
2192 goto error;
2193 }
2194
2195 /* XXX At this point, the default value (if there is one) has been read,
2196 * so the type of field is correct. If you depend on this type (for
2197 * example for check_attr_type_field()), your code should be below this
2198 * line. */
2199
2200 tab_for_each_pos(pos, attrs) {
2201 iopc_attr_t *attr = attrs->tab[pos];
2202
2203 if (check_attr_type_field(attr, f, false) < 0) {
2204 for (; pos < attrs->len; pos++) {
2205 iopc_attr_delete(&attrs->tab[pos]);
2206 }
2207 goto error;
2208 }
2209 qv_append(&f->attrs, attr);
2210 }
2211
2212 /* Looks for blacklisted keyword (after attribute has been parsed) */
2213 if (check_name(f->name, name_loc, &f->attrs) < 0) {
2214 goto error;
2215 }
2216
2217 iopc_loc_merge(&f->loc, TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc);
2218
2219 tag = f->tag;
2220 if (qm_add(iopc_field, fields, f->name, f)) {
2221 error_loc("field name `%s` is already in use", f->loc, f->name);
2222 goto error;
2223 }
2224
2225 if (f->is_static) {
2226 qv_append(&st->static_fields, f);
2227 return f;
2228 }
2229
2230 tab_for_each_entry(t, tags) {
2231 if (t == tag) {
2232 error_loc("tag %d is used twice", f->loc, tag);
2233 goto error;
2234 }
2235 }
2236 qv_append(tags, tag);
2237 qv_append(&st->fields, f);
2238 return f;
2239
2240 error:
2241 iopc_field_delete(&f);
2242 return NULL;
2243}
2244
2245static int check_snmp_brief(qv_t(iopc_dox) comments, iopc_loc_t loc,
2246 char *name, const char *type)
2247{
2248 tab_for_each_ptr(comment, &comments) {
2249 if (comment->type == IOPC_DOX_TYPE_BRIEF) {
2250 return 0;
2251 }
2252 }
2253 throw_loc("%s `%s` needs a brief that would be used as a "
2254 "description in the generated MIB", loc, type, name);
2255}
2256
2257static int check_snmp_tbl_has_index(iopc_struct_t *st)
2258{
2259 bool has_index = false;
2260
2261 tab_for_each_entry(field, &st->fields) {
2262 tab_for_each_entry(attr, &field->attrs) {
2263 if (attr->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_SNMP_INDEX) {
2264 has_index = true;
2265 }
2266 }
2267 }
2268
2269 if (!has_index) {
2270 throw_loc("each snmp table must contain at least one field that has "
2271 "attribute @snmpIndex of type 'uint' or 'string'", st->loc);
2272 }
2273
2274 return 0;
2275}
2276
2277static int parse_struct(iopc_parser_t *pp, iopc_struct_t *st, int sep,
2278 int paren, bool is_snmp_iface, bool is_rpc_arg)
2279{
2280 int res = 0;
2281 qm_t(iopc_field) fields = QM_INIT_CACHED(field, fields);
2282 int next_tag = 1;
2283 int next_field_pos = 0;
2284 int next_static_field_pos = 0;
2285 bool previous_static = true;
2286 qv_t(i32) tags;
2287 qv_t(iopc_attr) attrs;
2288 qv_t(dox_chunk) chunks;
2289
2290 qv_inita(&tags, 1024);
2291 qv_inita(&attrs, 16);
2292 qv_init(&chunks);
2293
2294 while (!CHECK_NOEOF(pp, 0, paren, goto error)) {
2295 iopc_field_t *f;
2296
2297 if (check_dox_and_attrs(pp, &chunks, &attrs) < 0
2298 || !(f = parse_field_stmt(pp, st, &attrs, &fields, &tags, &next_tag,
2299 paren, is_snmp_iface, is_rpc_arg)))
2300 {
2301 goto error;
2302 }
2303
2304 if (!previous_static && f->is_static) {
2305 error_loc("all static attributes must be declared first",
2306 TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc);
2307 goto error;
2308 }
2309 previous_static = f->is_static;
2310
2311 if (f->is_static) {
2312 f->field_pos = next_static_field_pos++;
2313 } else {
2314 f->field_pos = next_field_pos++;
2315 }
2316 RETHROW(read_dox_back(pp, &chunks, sep));
2317 RETHROW(build_dox_check_all(&chunks, f));
2318
2319 if (iopc_is_snmp_st(st->type)
2320 && check_snmp_brief(f->comments, f->loc, f->name, "field") < 0)
2321 {
2322 goto error;
2323 }
2324
2325 if (CHECK(pp, 0, paren, goto error)) {
2326 break;
2327 }
2328 if (__eat(pp, sep) < 0) {
2329 goto error;
2330 }
2331 }
2332
2333 if (st->type == STRUCT_TYPE_UNION && qm_len(iopc_field, &fields) == 0) {
2334 error_loc("a union must contain at least one field",
2335 TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc);
2336 goto error;
2337 }
2338
2339 if (iopc_is_snmp_tbl(st->type) && check_snmp_tbl_has_index(st) < 0) {
2340 goto error;
2341 }
2342
2343 iopc_loc_merge(&st->loc, TK(pp, 1, goto error)->loc);
2344
2345 end:
2346 qm_wipe(iopc_field, &fields);
2347 qv_wipe(&tags);
2348 qv_wipe(&attrs);
2349 qv_deep_wipe(&chunks, dox_chunk_wipe);
2350 return res;
2351
2352 error:
2353 res = -1;
2354 goto end;
2355}
2356
2357static int
2358check_class_or_snmp_obj_id_range(iopc_parser_t *pp, int struct_id,
2359 int min, int max)
2360{
2361 if (struct_id < min) {
2362 throw_loc("id is too small (must be >= %d, got %d)",
2363 TK_N(pp, 0)->loc, min, struct_id);
2364 }
2365 if (struct_id > max) {
2366 throw_loc("id is too large (must be <= %d, got %d)",
2367 TK_N(pp, 0)->loc, max, struct_id);
2368 }
2369 return 0;
2370}
2371
2372static int parse_handle_class_snmp(iopc_parser_t *pp, iopc_struct_t *st,
2373 bool is_main_pkg)
2374{
2375 iopc_token_t *tk;
2376 bool is_class = iopc_is_class(st->type);
2377
2378 assert (is_class || iopc_is_snmp_st(st->type));
2379
2380 /* Parse struct id; This is optional for a struct without parent, and
2381 * in this case default is 0. */
2382 if (SKIP_N(pp, ':')) {
2383 int id, pkg_min, pkg_max, global_min;
2384
2385 WANT(pp, 0, ITOK_INTEGER);
2386 tk = TK_N(pp, 0);
2387 st->class_id = tk->i; /* so st->snmp_obj_id is also set to tk->i */
2388
2389 if (is_class) {
2390 id = st->class_id;
2391 pkg_min = iopc_g.class_id_min;
2392 pkg_max = iopc_g.class_id_max;
2393 global_min = 0;
2394 } else {
2395 id = st->oid;
2396 pkg_min = SNMP_OBJ_OID_MIN;
2397 pkg_max = SNMP_OBJ_OID_MAX;
2398 global_min = 1;
2399 }
2400
2401 if (is_main_pkg) {
2402 RETHROW(check_class_or_snmp_obj_id_range(pp, id,
2403 pkg_min, pkg_max));
2404 } else {
2405 RETHROW(check_class_or_snmp_obj_id_range(pp, id,
2406 global_min, 0xFFFF));
2407 }
2408
2409 DROP(pp, 1);
2410
2411 /* Parse parent */
2412 if (SKIP_N(pp, ':')) {
2413 iopc_extends_t *xt = iopc_extends_new();
2414
2415 qv_append(&st->extends, xt);
2416 xt->loc = TK_N(pp, 0)->loc;
2417 RETHROW(parse_struct_type(pp, &xt->pkg, &xt->path, &xt->name));
2418 iopc_loc_merge(&xt->loc, TK_N(pp, 0)->loc);
2419
2420 /* Check if snmpObj parent is Intersec */
2421 xt->is_snmp_root = strequal(xt->name, "Intersec");
2422
2423 if (SKIP_N(pp, ',')) {
2424 throw_loc("multiple inheritance is not supported",
2425 TK_N(pp, 0)->loc);
2426 }
2427 } else
2428 if (iopc_is_snmp_st(st->type)) {
2429 throw_loc("%s `%s` needs a snmpObj parent", TK_N(pp, 0)->loc,
2430 iopc_struct_type_to_str(st->type), st->name);
2431 }
2432 } else
2433 if (iopc_is_snmp_st(st->type)) {
2434 throw_loc("%s `%s` needs a snmpObj parent", TK_N(pp, 0)->loc,
2435 iopc_struct_type_to_str(st->type), st->name);
2436 }
2437
2438 return 0;
2439}
2440
2441static int
2442parse_struct_class_union_snmp_stmt(iopc_parser_t *pp,
2443 iopc_struct_type_t type,
2444 bool is_abstract, bool is_local,
2445 bool is_main_pkg, iopc_struct_t *out)
2446{
2447 out->is_visible = true;
2448 out->type = type;
2449 out->name = RETHROW_PN(iopc_upper_ident(pp));
2450 out->loc = TK_N(pp, 0)->loc;
2451 out->is_abstract = is_abstract;
2452 out->is_local = is_local;
2453
2454 RETHROW(check_name(out->name, out->loc, &out->attrs));
2455
2456 if (iopc_is_class(out->type) || iopc_is_snmp_st(out->type)) {
2457 RETHROW(parse_handle_class_snmp(pp, out, is_main_pkg));
2458 }
2459
2460 if (!iopc_is_class(out->type)) {
2461 if (is_abstract) {
2462 throw_loc("only classes can be abstract", TK_N(pp, 0)->loc);
2463 }
2464 if (is_local) {
2465 throw_loc("only classes can be local", TK_N(pp, 0)->loc);
2466 }
2467 }
2468
2469 EAT(pp, '{');
2470 RETHROW(parse_struct(pp, out, ';', '}', false, false));
2471 EAT(pp, '}');
2472 EAT(pp, ';');
2473 return 0;
2474}
2475
2476static int __parse_enum_stmt(iopc_parser_t *pp, const qv_t(iopc_attr) *attrs,
2477 qv_t(i32) *values, qv_t(dox_chunk) *chunks,
2478 iopc_enum_t *out)
2479{
2480 t_scope;
2481 int64_t next_value = 0;
2482 lstr_t ns;
2483 lstr_t prefix = LSTR_NULL;
2484
2485 out->is_visible = true;
2486 out->loc = TK_N(pp, 0)->loc;
2487
2488 EAT_KW(pp, "enum");
2489 out->name = RETHROW_PN(iopc_upper_ident(pp));
2490 RETHROW(check_name(out->name, out->loc, &out->attrs));
2491 EAT(pp, '{');
2492
2493 t_iopc_attr_check_prefix(attrs, &prefix);
2494 lstr_ascii_toupper(&prefix);
2495
2496 ns = t_camelcase_to_c(LSTR(out->name));
2497 lstr_ascii_toupper(&ns);
2498
2499 if (lstr_equal(ns, prefix)) {
2500 prefix = LSTR_NULL_V;
2501 }
2502
2503 while (!CHECK_NOEOF_N(pp, 0, '}')) {
2504 iopc_enum_field_t *f = iopc_enum_field_new();
2505 char *ename;
2506
2507 if (check_dox_and_attrs(pp, chunks, &f->attrs) < 0
2508 || !(f->name = iopc_aupper_ident(pp)))
2509 {
2510 goto error;
2511 }
2512
2513 f->loc = TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc;
2514
2515 if (SKIP(pp, '=', goto error)) {
2516 if (parse_constant_integer(pp, '}', (uint64_t *)&next_value,
2517 NULL) < 0)
2518 {
2519 goto error;
2520 }
2521 }
2522
2523 tab_for_each_entry(attr, &f->attrs) {
2524 switch(attr->desc->id) {
2525 case IOPC_ATTR_GENERIC:
2526 break;
2527 case IOPC_ATTR_ALIAS:
2528 tab_for_each_entry(alias, &attr->args) {
2529 ename = asprintf("%*pM_%*pM", LSTR_FMT_ARG(ns),
2530 LSTR_FMT_ARG(alias.v.s));
2531 if (qm_add(enums, &_G.enums, ename, f)) {
2532 p_delete(&ename);
2533 error_loc("enum field alias `%*pM` is used twice",
2534 f->loc, LSTR_FMT_ARG(alias.v.s));
2535 goto error;
2536 }
2537 }
2538 break;
2539 default:
2540 error_loc("invalid attribute %s on enum field", f->loc,
2541 attr->desc->name.s);
2542 goto error;
2543 }
2544 }
2545
2546 /* handle properly prefixed enums */
2547 ename = asprintf("%*pM_%s", LSTR_FMT_ARG(ns), f->name);
2548 if (prefix.s) {
2549 uint32_t qpos = qm_put(enums, &_G.enums_forbidden, ename, f, 0);
2550
2551 if (qpos & QHASH_COLLISION) {
2552 p_delete(&ename);
2553 }
2554 ename = asprintf("%*pM_%s", LSTR_FMT_ARG(prefix), f->name);
2555 }
2556
2557 /* Checks for name uniqueness */
2558 if (qm_add(enums, &_G.enums, ename, f)) {
2559 p_delete(&ename);
2560 error_loc("enum field name `%s` is used twice", f->loc, f->name);
2561 goto error;
2562 }
2563
2564 f->value = next_value++;
2565 qv_append(&out->values, f);
2566 tab_for_each_entry(v, values) {
2567 if (v == f->value) {
2568 throw_loc("value %d is used twice", f->loc, f->value);
2569 }
2570 }
2571 qv_append(values, f->value);
2572
2573 RETHROW(read_dox_back(pp, chunks, ','));
2574 RETHROW(build_dox_check_all(chunks, f));
2575
2576 if (SKIP_N(pp, ',')) {
2577 continue;
2578 }
2579
2580 throw_loc("`,` expected on every line", f->loc);
2581
2582 error:
2583 iopc_enum_field_delete(&f);
2584 return -1;
2585 }
2586
2587 iopc_loc_merge(&out->loc, TK_N(pp, 1)->loc);
2588
2589 WANT(pp, 1, ';');
2590 DROP(pp, 2);
2591 return 0;
2592}
2593
2594static int parse_enum_stmt(iopc_parser_t *pp, const qv_t(iopc_attr) *attrs,
2595 iopc_enum_t *out)
2596{
2597 int res;
2598 qv_t(i32) values;
2599 qv_t(dox_chunk) chunks;
2600
2601 qv_inita(&values, 1024);
2602 qv_inita(&chunks, 16);
2603
2604 res = __parse_enum_stmt(pp, attrs, &values, &chunks, out);
2605
2606 qv_wipe(&values);
2607 qv_deep_wipe(&chunks, dox_chunk_wipe);
2608 return res;
2609}

2611static int parse_typedef_stmt(iopc_parser_t *pp, iopc_field_t *out)
2612{
2613 EAT_KW(pp, "typedef");
2614
2615 out->loc = TK_N(pp, 0)->loc;
2616 out->is_visible = true;
2617 RETHROW(parse_field_type(pp, NULL, out));
2618
2619 out->name = RETHROW_PN(iopc_upper_ident(pp));
2620 if (strchr(out->name, '_')) {
2621 throw_loc("identifer '%s' contains a _", TK_N(pp, 0)->loc, out->name);
2622 }
2623 EAT(pp, ';');
2624
2625 return 0;
2626}

2628static int parse_function_desc(iopc_parser_t *pp, iopc_fun_struct_type_t what,
2629 iopc_fun_t *fun, qv_t(dox_chunk) *chunks,
2630 iopc_iface_type_t iface_type, bool *res)
2631{
2632 static char const * const type_names[] = { "Args", "Res", "Exn", };
2633 static char const * const tokens[] = { "in", "out", "throw", };
2634 const char *type_name = type_names[what];
2635 const char *token = tokens[what];
2636 iopc_struct_t **sptr;
2637 iopc_field_t **fptr;
2638 bool is_snmp_iface = iopc_is_snmp_iface(iface_type);
2639
2640 *res = false;
2641
2642 RETHROW(read_dox_front(pp, chunks));
2643
2644 if (!CHECK_KW_N(pp, 0, token)) {
2645 return 0;
2646 }
2647
2648 if (fun->fun_is_async && (what == IOPC_FUN_EXN)) {
2649 throw_loc("async functions cannot throw", TK_N(pp, 0)->loc);
2650 }
2651 if (is_snmp_iface && (what == IOPC_FUN_EXN || what == IOPC_FUN_RES)) {
2652 throw_loc("snmpIface cannot out and/or throw", TK_N(pp, 0)->loc);
2653 }
2654
2655 DROP(pp, 1);
2656 if (SKIP_N(pp, '(')) {
2657 iopc_fun_struct_t *fun_st;
2658
2659 fun_st = iopc_fun_get_struct(fun, what);
2660 if (!fun_st) {
2661 abort();
2662 }
2663 fun_st->is_anonymous = true;
2664 sptr = &fun_st->anonymous_struct;
2665 *sptr = iopc_struct_new();
2666 (*sptr)->name = asprintf("%s%s", fun->name, type_name);
2667 (*sptr)->loc = TK_N(pp, 0)->loc;
2668 RETHROW(parse_struct(pp, *sptr, ',', ')', is_snmp_iface, true));
2669 EAT(pp, ')');
2670 RETHROW(read_dox_back(pp, chunks, 0));
2671 RETHROW(build_dox_check_all(chunks, *sptr));
2672 } else /* fname in void ... */
2673 if (CHECK_KW_N(pp, 0, "void")) {
2674 if (is_snmp_iface) {
2675 throw_loc("void is not supported by snmpIface RPCs",
2676 TK_N(pp, 0)->loc);
2677 }
2678 DROP(pp, 1);
2679 } else
2680 if (is_snmp_iface && SKIP_KW_N(pp, "null")) {
2681 throw_loc("null is not supported by snmpIface RPCs",
2682 TK_N(pp, 0)->loc);
2683 } else
2684 if ((what == IOPC_FUN_RES) && SKIP_KW_N(pp, "null")) {
2685 fun->fun_is_async = true;
2686 } else
2687 if (is_snmp_iface) {
2688 throw_loc("snmpIface RPC argument must be anonymous. example "
2689 "`in (a, b, c);`", TK_N(pp, 0)->loc);
2690 } else { /* fname in Type ... */
2691 iop_type_t type = get_type_kind(TK_N(pp, 0));
2692 iopc_field_t *f;
2693 iopc_fun_struct_t *fun_st;
2694
2695 if (type != IOP_T_STRUCT) {
2696 throw_loc("a structure (or a union) type was expected here"
2697 " (got %s)", TK_N(pp, 0)->loc, ident(TK_N(pp, 0)));
2698 }
2699
2700 /* We use a field to store the type of the function argument. */
2701 fun_st = iopc_fun_get_struct(fun, what);
2702 if (!fun_st) {
2703 abort();
2704 }
2705 fun_st->is_anonymous = false;
2706 fptr = &fun_st->existing_struct;
2707
2708 f = iopc_field_new();
2709 *fptr = f;
2710
2711 f->name = asprintf("%s%s", fun->name, type_name);
2712 f->loc = TK_N(pp, 0)->loc;
2713 f->kind = IOP_T_STRUCT;
2714
2715 RETHROW(parse_struct_type(pp, &f->type_pkg, &f->type_path,
2716 &f->type_name));
2717
2718 RETHROW(read_dox_back(pp, chunks, 0));
2719 RETHROW(build_dox_check_all(chunks, f));
2720
2721 iopc_loc_merge(&f->loc, TK_N(pp, 0)->loc);
2722 }
2723
2724 qv_deep_clear(chunks, dox_chunk_wipe);
2725 *res = true;
2726 return 0;
2727}
2728
2729static iopc_fun_t *
2730parse_function_stmt(iopc_parser_t *pp, qv_t(iopc_attr) *attrs,
2731 qv_t(i32) *tags, int *next_tag,
2732 iopc_iface_type_t type)
2733{
2734 SB_1k(err);
2735 iopc_fun_t *fun = iopc_fun_new();
2736 iopc_token_t *tk;
2737 int tag;
2738 qv_t(dox_chunk) fun_chunks, arg_chunks;
2739 bool res_res;
2740 bool exn_res;
2741
2742 qv_init(&fun_chunks);
2743 qv_init(&arg_chunks);
2744
2745 if ((check_dox_and_attrs)(pp, &fun_chunks, attrs, IOPC_ATTR_T_RPC) < 0) {
2746 goto error;
2747 }
2748
2749 fun->loc = TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc;
2750 if (CHECK(pp, 0, ITOK_INTEGER, goto error)) {
2751 if (__want(pp, 1, ':') < 0) {
2752 goto error;
2753 }
2754 tk = TK(pp, 0, goto error);
2755 fun->tag = tk->i;
2756 *next_tag = fun->tag + 1;
2757 DROP(pp, 2);
2758 } else {
2759 fun->tag = (*next_tag)++;
2760 }
2761 if (iopc_check_tag_value(fun->tag, &err) < 0) {
2762 error_loc("%*pM", TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc, SB_FMT_ARG(&err));
2763 goto error;
2764 }
2765
2766 qv_extend_tab(&fun->attrs, attrs);
2767
2768 if (!(fun->name = iopc_lower_ident(pp))
2769 || check_name(fun->name, TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc, &fun->attrs) < 0
2770 || read_dox_back(pp, &fun_chunks, 0) < 0)
2771 {
2772 goto error;
2773 }
2774
2775 /* Parse function desc */
2776 if (parse_function_desc(pp, IOPC_FUN_ARGS, fun, &arg_chunks, type,
2777 &res_res) < 0)
2778 {
2779 goto error;
2780 }
2781 if (parse_function_desc(pp, IOPC_FUN_RES, fun, &arg_chunks, type,
2782 &res_res) < 0
2783 || parse_function_desc(pp, IOPC_FUN_EXN, fun, &arg_chunks, type,
2784 &exn_res) < 0)
2785 {
2786 goto error;
2787 }
2788 if (!res_res && !exn_res && !iopc_is_snmp_iface(type)) {
2789 error_loc("no `out` nor `throw` for function `%s`",
2790 fun->loc, fun->name);
2791 goto error;
2792 }
2793
2794 if (__eat(pp, ';') < 0) {
2795 goto error;
2796 }
2797
2798 tag = fun->tag;
2799 for (int i = 0; i < tags->len; i++) {
2800 if (tags->tab[i] == tag) {
2801 error_loc("tag %d is used twice", fun->loc, tag);
2802 goto error;
2803 }
2804 }
2805 qv_append(tags, tag);
2806
2807 if (build_dox(&fun_chunks, fun, IOPC_ATTR_T_RPC) < 0) {
2808 goto error;
2809 }
2810 if (iopc_is_snmp_iface(type)) {
2811 if (check_snmp_brief(fun->comments, fun->loc, fun->name,
2812 "notification") < 0)
2813 {
2814 goto error;
2815 }
2816 }
2817
2818 qv_deep_wipe(&fun_chunks, dox_chunk_wipe);
2819 qv_deep_wipe(&arg_chunks, dox_chunk_wipe);
2820 return fun;
2821
2822 error:
2823 iopc_fun_delete(&fun);
2824 qv_deep_wipe(&fun_chunks, dox_chunk_wipe);
2825 qv_deep_wipe(&arg_chunks, dox_chunk_wipe);
2826 return NULL;
2827}

2829static int parse_snmp_iface_parent(iopc_parser_t *pp, iopc_iface_t *iface,
2830 bool is_main_pkg)
2831{
2832 iopc_token_t *tk;
2833
2834 /* Check OID */
2835 if (SKIP_N(pp, ':')) {
2836 WANT(pp, 0, ITOK_INTEGER);
2837 tk = TK_N(pp, 0);
2838
2839 iface->oid = tk->i;
2840
2841 if (is_main_pkg) {
2842 RETHROW(check_class_or_snmp_obj_id_range(pp, iface->oid,
2843 SNMP_IFACE_OID_MIN,
2844 SNMP_IFACE_OID_MAX));
2845 } else {
2846 RETHROW(check_class_or_snmp_obj_id_range(pp, iface->oid,
2847 0, 0xFFFF));
2848 }
2849 DROP(pp, 1);
2850 }
2851
2852 /* Parse parent */
2853 if (SKIP_N(pp, ':')) {
2854 iopc_extends_t *xt = iopc_extends_new();
2855
2856 qv_append(&iface->extends, xt);
2857
2858 xt->loc = TK_N(pp, 0)->loc;
2859 RETHROW(parse_struct_type(pp, &xt->pkg, &xt->path, &xt->name));
2860 iopc_loc_merge(&xt->loc, TK_N(pp, 0)->loc);
2861
2862 if (SKIP_N(pp, ',')) {
2863 throw_loc("multiple inheritance is not supported",
2864 TK_N(pp, 0)->loc);
2865 }
2866 } else {
2867 throw_loc("snmpIface `%s` needs a snmpObj parent", TK_N(pp, 0)->loc,
2868 iface->name);
2869 }
2870 return 0;
2871}

2873static iopc_iface_t *parse_iface_stmt(iopc_parser_t *pp,
2874 iopc_iface_type_t type,
2875 const char *name, bool is_main_pkg)
2876{
2877 qm_t(iopc_fun) funs = QM_INIT_CACHED(fun, funs);
2878 qv_t(i32) tags;
2879 qv_t(iopc_attr) attrs;
2880 int next_tag = 1;
2881 iopc_iface_t *iface = iopc_iface_new();
2882
2883 qv_inita(&tags, 1024);
2884 qv_inita(&attrs, 16);
2885
2886 iface->loc = TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc;
2887 iface->type = type;
2888
2889 if (__eat_kw(pp, name) < 0
2890 || !(iface->name = iopc_upper_ident(pp)))
2891 {
2892 goto error;
2893 }
2894
2895 if (check_name(iface->name, iface->loc, &iface->attrs) < 0) {
2896 goto error;
2897 }
2898
2899 if (iopc_is_snmp_iface(type)
2900 && parse_snmp_iface_parent(pp, iface, is_main_pkg) < 0)
2901 {
2902 goto error;
2903 }
2904
2905 if (__eat(pp, '{') < 0) {
2906 goto error;
2907 }
2908
2909 while (!CHECK_NOEOF(pp, 0, '}', goto error)) {
2910 iopc_fun_t *fun;
2911
2912 fun = parse_function_stmt(pp, &attrs, &tags, &next_tag, iface->type);
2913 if (!fun) {
2914 goto error;
2915 }
2916 qv_append(&iface->funs, fun);
2917 fun->pos = iface->funs.len;
2918 if (qm_add(iopc_fun, &funs, fun->name, fun)) {
2919 error_loc("a function `%s` already exists", fun->loc, fun->name);
2920 goto error;
2921 }
2922 }
2923
2924 iopc_loc_merge(&iface->loc, TK(pp, 1, goto error)->loc);
2925 if (__want(pp, 1, ';') < 0) {
2926 goto error;
2927 }
2928 DROP(pp, 2);
2929
2930 qm_wipe(iopc_fun, &funs);
2931 qv_wipe(&tags);
2932 qv_wipe(&attrs);
2933 return iface;
2934
2935 error:
2936 qm_wipe(iopc_fun, &funs);
2937 qv_wipe(&tags);
2938 qv_wipe(&attrs);
2939 iopc_iface_delete(&iface);
2940 return NULL;
2941}

2943static iopc_field_t *
2944parse_mod_field_stmt(iopc_parser_t *pp, iopc_struct_t *mod,
2945 qm_t(iopc_field) *fields, qv_t(i32) *tags, int *next_tag)
2946{
2947 SB_1k(err);
2948 iopc_field_t *f = NULL;
2949 iopc_token_t *tk;
2950 int tag;
2951
2952 f = iopc_field_new();
2953 qv_append(&mod->fields, f);
2954 f->loc = TK_P(pp, 0)->loc;
2955
2956 if (CHECK_P(pp, 0, ITOK_INTEGER)) {
2957 WANT_P(pp, 1, ':');
2958 tk = TK_P(pp, 0);
2959 f->tag = tk->i;
2960 *next_tag = f->tag + 1;
2961 DROP(pp, 2);
2962 } else {
2963 f->tag = (*next_tag)++;
2964 }
2965
2966 if (iopc_check_tag_value(f->tag, &err) < 0) {
2967 throw_loc_p("%*pM", TK_P(pp, 0)->loc, SB_FMT_ARG(&err));
2968 }
2969
2970 RETHROW_NP(parse_struct_type(pp, &f->type_pkg, &f->type_path,
2971 &f->type_name));
2972 f->name = RETHROW_P(iopc_lower_ident(pp));
2973 if (strchr(f->name, '_')) {
2974 throw_loc_p("identifier '%s' contains a _",
2975 TK_P(pp, 0)->loc, f->name);
2976 }
2977
2978 iopc_loc_merge(&f->loc, TK_P(pp, 0)->loc);
2979
2980 tag = f->tag;
2981 if (qm_add(iopc_field, fields, f->name, f)) {
2982 throw_loc_p("field name `%s` is already in use", f->loc, f->name);
2983 }
2984 for (int i = 0; i < tags->len; i++) {
2985 if (tags->tab[i] == tag) {
2986 throw_loc_p("tag %d is used twice", f->loc, tag);
2987 }
2988 }
2989 qv_append(tags, tag);
2990 return f;
2991}

2993static iopc_struct_t *parse_module_stmt(iopc_parser_t *pp)
2994{
2995 int next_tag = 1;
2996 qm_t(iopc_field) fields = QM_INIT_CACHED(field, fields);
2997 qv_t(i32) tags;
2998 iopc_struct_t *mod = iopc_struct_new();
2999 qv_t(dox_chunk) chunks;
3000
3001 qv_inita(&chunks, 16);
3002 qv_inita(&tags, 1024);
3003
3004 mod->loc = TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc;
3005
3006 if (__eat_kw(pp, "module") < 0
3007 || !(mod->name = iopc_upper_ident(pp)))
3008 {
3009 goto error;
3010 }
3011
3012 if (SKIP(pp, ':', goto error)) {
3013 do {
3014 iopc_extends_t *xt = iopc_extends_new();
3015
3016 qv_append(&mod->extends, xt);
3017 xt->loc = TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc;
3018 if (parse_struct_type(pp, &xt->pkg, &xt->path, &xt->name) < 0) {
3019 goto error;
3020 }
3021 iopc_loc_merge(&xt->loc, TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc);
3022 } while (SKIP(pp, ',', goto error));
3023 if (CHECK(pp, 0, ';', goto error)) {
3024 goto empty_body;
3025 }
3026 }
3027 if (__eat(pp, '{') < 0) {
3028 goto error;
3029 }
3030
3031 while (!CHECK_NOEOF(pp, 0, '}', goto error)) {
3032 iopc_field_t *f;
3033
3034 if (read_dox_front(pp, &chunks) < 0
3035 || !(f = parse_mod_field_stmt(pp, mod, &fields, &tags, &next_tag))
3036 || read_dox_back(pp, &chunks, ';') < 0
3037 || build_dox_check_all(&chunks, f) < 0)
3038 {
3039 goto error;
3040 }
3041 if (__eat(pp, ';') < 0) {
3042 goto error;
3043 }
3044 }
3045 DROP(pp, 1);
3046
3047 empty_body:
3048 iopc_loc_merge(&mod->loc, TK(pp, 0, goto error)->loc);
3049 if (__eat(pp, ';') < 0) {
3050 goto error;
3051 }
3052 end:
3053 qm_wipe(iopc_field, &fields);
3054 qv_wipe(&tags);
3055 qv_deep_wipe(&chunks, dox_chunk_wipe);
3056 return mod;
3057
3058 error:
3059 iopc_struct_delete(&mod);
3060 goto end;
3061}

3063static int parse_json_array(iopc_parser_t *pp, sb_t *sb);
3064
3065static int parse_json_value(iopc_parser_t *pp, sb_t *sb)
3066{
3067 SB_1k(tmp);
3068 iopc_token_t *tk = TK_N(pp, 0);
3069
3070 switch (tk->token) {
3071 case ITOK_STRING:
3072 sb_add_slashes(&tmp, tk->b.data, tk->b.len,
3073 "\a\b\e\t\n\v\f\r\"", "abetnvfr\"");
3074 sb_addf(sb, "\"%*pM\"", SB_FMT_ARG(&tmp));
3075 break;
3076
3077 case ITOK_INTEGER:
3078 if (tk->i_is_signed) {
3079 sb_addf(sb, "%jd", tk->i);
3080 } else {
3081 sb_addf(sb, "%ju", tk->i);
3082 }
3083 break;
3084
3085 case ITOK_DOUBLE:
3086 sb_addf(sb, DOUBLE_FMT, tk->d);
3087 break;
3088
3089 case ITOK_LBRACE:
3090 return parse_json_object(pp, sb, false);
3091
3092 case ITOK_LBRACKET:
3093 return parse_json_array(pp, sb);
3094
3095 case ITOK_BOOL:
3096 sb_addf(sb, "%s", tk->i ? "true" : "false");
3097 break;
3098
3099 case ITOK_IDENT:
3100 if (CHECK_KW_N(pp, 0, "null")) {
3101 sb_adds(sb, "null");
3102 } else {
3103 throw_loc("invalid identifier when parsing json value", tk->loc);
3104 }
3105 break;
3106
3107 default:
3108 throw_loc("invalid token when parsing json value", tk->loc);
3109 break;
3110 }
3111
3112 DROP(pp, 1);
3113 return 0;
3114}
3115
3116static int parse_json_array(iopc_parser_t *pp, sb_t *sb)
3117{
3118 EAT(pp, '[');
3119 sb_addc(sb, '[');
3120
3121 if (CHECK_NOEOF_N(pp, 0, ']')) {
3122 goto end;
3123 }
3124 for (;;) {
3125 RETHROW(parse_json_value(pp, sb));
3126
3127 if (!CHECK_N(pp, 0, ',')) {
3128 break;
3129 }
3130 DROP(pp, 1);
3131 if (CHECK_NOEOF_N(pp, 0, ']')) {
3132 break;
3133 }
3134 sb_addc(sb, ',');
3135 }
3136 end:
3137 EAT(pp, ']');
3138 sb_addc(sb, ']');
3139 return 0;
3140}
3141
3142static int parse_json_object(iopc_parser_t *pp, sb_t *sb, bool toplevel)
3143{
3144 char end = toplevel ? ')' : '}';
3145
3146 if (!toplevel) {
3147 EAT(pp, '{');
3148 sb_addc(sb, '{');
3149 }
3150 if (CHECK_NOEOF_N(pp, 0, end)) {
3151 goto end;
3152 }
3153 for (;;) {
3154 iopc_token_t *tk = TK_N(pp, 0);
3155
3156 if (!CHECK_N(pp, 0, ITOK_IDENT)) {
3157 WANT(pp, 0, ITOK_STRING);
3158 }
3159 sb_addf(sb, "\"%*pM\"", SB_FMT_ARG(&tk->b));
3160 DROP(pp, 1);
3161
3162 if (CHECK_N(pp, 0, '=')) {
3163 DROP(pp, 1);
3164 } else {
3165 EAT(pp, ':');
3166 }
3167 sb_addc(sb, ':');
3168
3169 RETHROW(parse_json_value(pp, sb));
3170
3171 if (!CHECK_N(pp, 0, ',')) {
3172 break;
3173 }
3174 DROP(pp, 1);
3175 if (CHECK_NOEOF_N(pp, 0, end)) {
3176 break;
3177 }
3178 sb_addc(sb, ',');
3179 }
3180 end:
3181 if (!toplevel) {
3182 EAT(pp, '}');
3183 sb_addc(sb, '}');
3184 }
3185 return 0;
3186}

3188static int parse_gen_attr_arg(iopc_parser_t *pp, iopc_attr_t *attr,
3189 iopc_arg_desc_t *desc, lstr_t *out)
3190{
3191 SB_1k(sb);
3192 iopc_arg_t arg;
3193 iopc_token_t *tk;
3194
3195 assert (IOPC_ATTR_REPEATED_MONO_ARG(attr->desc));
3196 if (!expect(desc)) {
3197 return -1;
3198 }
3199
3200 iopc_arg_init(&arg);
3201 arg.desc = desc;
3202 arg.loc = TK_N(pp, 0)->loc;
3203
3204 WANT(pp, 0, ITOK_GEN_ATTR_NAME);
3205 *out = lstr_dups(TK_N(pp, 0)->b.data, -1);
3206 DROP(pp, 1);
3207
3208 if (!CHECK_N(pp, 0, ',')) {
3209 /* Consider @(name) as an empty JSON */
3210 arg.type = ITOK_IDENT;
3211 arg.v.s = LSTR("{}");
3212 goto append;
3213 }
3214 EAT(pp, ',');
3215
3216 tk = TK_N(pp, 0);
3217 arg.type = tk->token;
3218
3219 if (CHECK_N(pp, 1, ':') || CHECK_N(pp, 1, '=')) {
3220 arg.type = ITOK_IDENT;
3221 sb_addc(&sb, '{');
3222 RETHROW(parse_json_object(pp, &sb, true));
3223 sb_addc(&sb, '}');
3224 lstr_transfer_sb(&arg.v.s, &sb, false);
3225 goto append;
3226 }
3227
3228 switch (arg.type) {
3229 case ITOK_STRING:
3230 arg.v.s = lstr_dups(tk->b.data, -1);
3231 break;
3232
3233 case ITOK_DOUBLE:
3234 arg.v.d = tk->d;
3235 break;
3236
3237 case ITOK_INTEGER:
3238 case ITOK_BOOL:
3239 arg.v.i64 = tk->i;
3240 break;
3241
3242 default:
3243 throw_loc("unable to parse value for generic argument '%*pM'",
3244 TK_N(pp, 0)->loc, LSTR_FMT_ARG(*out));
3245 }
3246
3247 DROP(pp, 1);
3248
3249 append:
3250 qv_append(&attr->args, arg);
3251 return 0;
3252}
